# The Bright Brand visual identity

This is the **default** for every TBB page, section and component. Treat it as the starting point, not a cage. If I ask for something different in chat, my instruction wins. Do not argue the brand back at me once I have asked to deviate.

## Defaults (apply unless I say otherwise)

- Dark theme only. Base `#060A10`, surfaces `#080D16`, cards `rgba(255,255,255,0.04)` with `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` borders, radius 12px.
- Text is white. Body copy is white at 50 percent. Headings white at full.
- Blue `#5B9FFF` is an accent only: labels, links, small highlights. Never a fill, never a button background, never dominant.
- Inter is the only typeface. Headings Semibold 600, capitalised. Labels Bold 700, uppercase, blue, wide tracking, wrapped in brackets: `[ LIKE THIS ]`.
- Every surface gets the subtle white grid. Every hero or full-width section gets one blue radial glow in the top right corner.
- Green `#34D399` for positive metrics, red `#FB7185` for negative or alerts. Nothing else.

## Working from reference images

When I drop in a screenshot or a link to another site, treat it as **layout and interaction inspiration only**. Borrow the structure: section order, grid, spacing rhythm, component ideas, motion. Never carry over their colours, fonts or styling. Rebuild everything in the tokens above. The output should look like The Bright Brand, not like the reference.

## Exact tokens and CSS

The full palette, grid and glow CSS, type scale and the bracket Label component live in `docs/BRANDING.md`. Read that file before building any page.
